Boil the potatoes for about 10 minutes, or until slightly softHeat the oil in a frying pan. Once hot, add the cooked potatoes, mushrooms and peppers (or other vegetables of your choice). Once the vegetables are soft and slightly browned, transfer to a bowl.Add the beaten eggs to the pan. When the eggs have set slightly, return the vegetable mixture to the pan. Sprinkle some cheese on topFlip the omelette to cook the other side, or fold the omelette in half. Serve with salad.